Install Express:
In your project directory, run npm install express to install Express and save it as a dependency in package.json.
npm install express

Create index.js:
Create an index.js file in your project directory and add the following code to set up a basic Express server.
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const port = 3000;

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello, World!');
});

app.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(`Server is running at http://localhost:${port}`);
});

Run the Application:
Use npm start to run the application (as defined in the scripts section of package.json)
npm start
